Drain the @king prawns{225%grams}. Heat a drizzle of @oil{a drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the prawns. Season with @salt and @pepper and stir-fry for ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once cooked, remove the pan from the heat and allow to cool while you prep the rest of the recipe.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

While the prawns cook, zest and quarter the @lemon{1}. Juice half the lemon into a #large bowl{}. Set aside the remaining 2 wedges of lemon for the end.

In a #medium bowl{} combine the @mayonnaise{64%grams}, @tomato ketchup{1/2%tsp} and @sugar for the sauce{1/2%tsp}. Add a pinch of lemon zest, a pinch of @smoked paprika{1%tsp} (add more if you prefer) and half a tsp of lemon juice from the large bowl. Season with @salt and @pepper.

Trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}, halve lengthways, then thinly slice.

== Dressing ==

To the bowl of lemon juice, add the @olive oil{1%tbsp} and @sugar for the dressing{1/2%tsp}, then season with @salt and @pepper. Add the lettuce to the lemon dressing and toss to coat.

Once the prawns are cooked, add them to the marie-rose sauce and mix to coat.

Divide the dressed lettuce between your #serving glasses{}, then top with the prawns.

Sprinkle over a pinch of lemon zest and a pinch of smoked paprika, then serve with the remaining lemon wedges, on the side of the glass, for squeezing over, to finish.